Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Trim the @aubergine{1}, then halve lengthways. Cut each half into four long strips,
then widthways into thirds.

Pop the aubergine onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast the aubergine on the top shelf until soft and
golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Pop half the @garlic cloves{4}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a
drizzle of @oil and scrunch to enclose it. Roast the parcel on a baking tray
on the middle shelf of your oven until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the remaining garlic (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium heat. Melt in the
@butter{20%g}.

When hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{1%minute}, then stir in the
@couscous{120%g} until coated, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{300%ml}. Bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to the side
for ~{8-10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

When your roasted garlic is ready, remove the parcel from the baking tray and
allow to cool slightly.

Place the @ready to eat falafels{171%g} onto the (now empty) baking tray and
bake on the middle shelf until golden brown, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Once the garlic has cooled, cut the end with #scissors{}, squeeze it out of the
skin and mash with a #fork{}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine the mashed garlic and @greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

When the aubergine has 5 mins left, drizzle over the @honey{1%tbsp} and toss to
coat. Return to the oven and bake for the remaining time until golden and
sticky.

When the couscous is cooked, stir through the @Zhoug style paste{50%g} and
tomato chunks. Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if needed.

> Add less zhoug if you'd prefer things milder.

Share your couscous between your #serving bowls{} and top with the falafels and
honey roasted aubergine.

Spoon the garlic yoghurt over the falafels to finish.

Enjoy!